    <fr:anchor>12083</fr:anchor>
    <fr:addr type="user">//forester/jms-0067</fr:addr>
    <fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-0067.xml</fr:route>
    <fr:title text="Forester 2.2 › flexible transclusion options"><fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-005V.xml" title="Forester 2.2" addr="//forester/jms-005V" type="local">Forester 2.2</fr:link> › flexible transclusion options</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>This release replaces the old <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude*]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude@]]></fr:code> commands with a more flexible transclusion configuration mechanism using the support for fluid binding introduced in <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-005O.xml" title="Forester 2.1" addr="//forester/jms-005O" type="local">Forester 2.1</fr:link>. A basic transclusion with the default options is done in the same way as before:</fr:p>
    <fr:pre><![CDATA[\transclude{jms-0005}]]></fr:pre>
    <fr:p>The behavior of transclusion is, however, configurable by several globally allocated fluid bindings as depicted in the <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jms-0069.xml" title="Transclusion options" addr="//forester/jms-0069" type="local">table below</fr:link>.</fr:p>
    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:authors>
          <fr:author>
            <fr:link href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//forester/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
          </fr:author>
        </fr:authors>
